The generic line is rotated N-times which create N slices
or levels. The M edges of the line generate N*M quadrangles.

If a vertex of the line is on the rotation axis, the edge
with this vertex, produces a triangle.

The total rotation angle can reach 360 degrees.

Example:
S15.1; I; 15; INITIAL_LINE; P1_AXIS; P2_AXIS; 4; {rotations}
1; {angle for each rotation}
20; 30; 40; 50; {variable angles}
{The rotations add from the initial line}

Define a surface by 4 successive rotations of 20, 50, 90
and 140 degrees of the initial line around the axis defined by the
points P1_AXIS and P2_AXIS
